            <div class="about-main">
                <h3>Professional Summary</h3>
                <p>
                    I am an accomplished academic and public health professional with a PhD and a passion for innovative teaching and research. As a well-organized and creative educator, I am guided by a student-centered teaching philosophy that integrates technology, active learning, and real-world applications.
                </p>
                <p>
                    My research interests focus on public health genomics, pharmacogenomics implementation, and digital health. I have been recognized with an Excellence in Teaching Award (2025) for outstanding student evaluations and pioneering use of AI in the classroom.
                </p>
                <p>
                    I hold multiple faculty fellowships and editorial roles, with a strong record of peer-reviewed publications in Q1 journals and successful grant acquisition totaling over AED 1,063,000 as PI/Co-PI.
                </p>

                <div class="philosophy-box">
                    <h4>"It is my aspiration to make students grow and excel."</h4>
                    <p style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem; font-style: italic;">My teaching is built on five pillars:</p>
